h3. Issue Summary

Classic scrum board do not set the right component when we switch from Board A to Board B.
h3. Steps to Reproduce

Note: This behavior is reproducible on Scrum Boards.
 # Create two *components* as "*Board A*" and "*Board B*";
 # Create two boards with the exact same name "*Board A*" and "*Board B*";
 # Now, access one of the boards and refresh the Page;
 # Create a new issue and the Component should be automatically set on the issue. For example, for Board "*Board A*", it will set Component "*Board A*";
 # Now, switch to the board "*Board B*" and create a new issue, component "*Board A*" will be set;
 # Refresh the page on board "*Board B*" and create one more issue. Now Component "*Board B*" will be set;
 # Switch to board "*Board A*" without refreshing and create an issue. Component "*Board B*" will be set;
 # Refresh and create another issue on Board "*Board A*", Component "*Board A*" will be set.

 * Video with steps to reproduce the error and with the bug behavior: [Click here to see the bug behavior.|https://share.getcloudapp.com/nOukB4RK]

h3. Expected Results

When we switch from Board A to Board B, it should set the component B instead of component A.
h3. Actual Results

When we switch from Board A to Board B, if you create an issue, component A will be set instead of component B. It seems that until we refresh the page, we are keeping the session in the previous board and this is causing the incorrect component to be set.
h3. Workaround

When we change from Board A to Board B we need to refresh the board to the right component be set.

When managing multiple teams and boards, it is impractical to manually update each sprint and start/end them individually.  It would be much nicer if we could have the following features included in the future;


 # The ability to add start and end dates to future sprints.
 # The ability to select to automatically start and end sprints based on those dates on a Project-basis (wherever the sprint is housed).
